\displaystyle S_n = \sum_{k=1}^{n} k
\implies 2 S_n = 2 (1 + 2 + 3 + \ldots (n-1) + n)
\implies 2 S_n = (1 + 2 + 3 + \ldots (n-1) + n) + (n + (n-1) + \ldots + 3 + 2 + 1)
\implies 2 S_n = (1+n) + (2+(n-2)) + (3+(n-3)) + \ldots + (n-1 + 1) + (n+1)
\implies 2 S_n = n(n+1)
